=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Guides_Tour_of_UGens_ex61 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark clean sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 434 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: clean
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 433.6907
  harmonic_decay_rate: -11.1839
  harmonic_regularity: 0.7002
  pitch_clarity: 86.5200
  inharmonicity: 0.2617
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -8.9181
  resonance_freq: 452.1973

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Tour of UGens Example 61
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Guides/Tour_of_UGens.html
// Tags: Tour_of_UGens, Guides
// ---
// --- Example 61 ---
{ WhiteNoise.ar * Decay.ar(Impulse.ar(1), 0.9, 0.2) }.play;
{ WhiteNoise.ar * Decay.ar(Dust.ar(3), 0.9, 0.2) }.play;
{ SinOsc.ar(Decay.ar(Dust.ar(4), 0.5, 1000, 400), 0, 0.2) }.play;
